# Project: ManyChat-style Prototype
# Stack: React 18 + TypeScript + Ant Design 5 + Styled Components + Vite

## Design System Rules
- Use Ant Design components as the base layer
- Use Styled Components to extend/customize Ant components
- Never use inline styles
- Never use plain CSS files
- Wrap Ant components with styled() when customizing

## Theme
- Primary color: #0084FF (ManyChat blue)
- Secondary color: #7B61FF (purple accent)
- Sidebar background: #1B2559 (dark navy)
- Sidebar active: rgba(255,255,255,0.1)
- Success: #22C55E
- Warning: #F59E0B
- Error: #EF4444
- Border radius: 8px default, 12px for cards
- Font: Inter, -apple-system, sans-serif

## Component Conventions
- One component per file
- Named exports only
- Styled components defined above the main component in the same file
- Props interface defined above the component
- File name matches component name: StatCard.tsx → export const StatCard

## Responsive Breakpoints
- Mobile: max-width 768px
- Tablet: max-width 1024px
- Desktop: min-width 1025px
- Sidebar collapses to bottom nav on mobile

## File Structure
- components/layout/ → AppShell, Sidebar, TopBar, MobileNav
- components/dashboard/ → Dashboard screen components
- components/shared/ → Reusable across screens
- styles/ → theme.ts, globalStyles.ts, mixins.ts
- data/mock/ → Mock data files

## Code Style
- Functional components only
- Use React.FC sparingly — prefer typed props
- Destructure props in function signature
- Keep components under 150 lines — split if larger
